title: Oxford University - 124 Very Short Introductions
description:
Also here:
Oxford University Press publishes a series of short books collectively called Very Short Introductions, that thoroughly focuses on the humanities and arts. No... you won't find too much Mathematics in here. The notable exception is the Particle Physics Introduction.

Here are 123 out of the 206 published books as of July 9, 2009. I've read a few - they are really enjoyable to read. The 124th one is called "Everything", which comes with every box set that they sell (you can't buy it separately).

The indented files are the one's we haven't pirated yet!
